<|startoftext|>Dish: chocolate chip raspberry scones  gluten free
Directions: preheat oven to 425f
line two 8 inch-diameter disposable baking paper towels with paper towels
sift flour , baking powder , baking soda , and salt into a large bowl
cut in shortening at the same time , mixing with a wooden spoon to ensure ingredients are thoroughly incorporated
gently stir in chips except 1 / 2 cup toasted almonds
roll dough into a very tightly rolled rectangle about 10 inches by 13 inches
spread 1 / 4 teaspoon of the toasted almonds on one corner of each rectangle
sprinkle 1 / 4 teaspoon of flour all over dough
lay 2 cookies , overlapping slightly , in the center and working quickly , press dough onto each cookie
continue rolling dough on the cookie cutouts until dough is very thin
using a serrated knife or pastry brush , mark each scone into 6 equal triangles
cut each triangle with a serrated knife into quarters , placing on a baking sheet
repeat with remaining scones
bake scones for 15 to 18 minutes , or until golden brown
cool scones on the baking sheet for 2 minutes , then remove to a wire rack
serve warm or at room temperature'<|endoftext|>
